    "steps": [
        "To make scallion and ginger liquid, chop the top half of the spring onions. Roughly cut up the onion greens and slice some ginger, and rub them in a bowl of water until the water turns green.",
        "Thinly slice the rest of the green onions and submerge them in a bowl of water.",
        "Thinly slice the pork and mix with the marinade. Add the cornstach after the meat has absorbed all the liquid.",
        "In a hot wok, add 3 tbsp oil and stir fry the pork until 90% cooked through. Remove from wok and set aside.",
        "In a clean wok, add 1 tbsp oil and sweet bean sauce and stir at medium high heat to bring out the fragrance. After 30-60s, add in the remaining sauce.",
        "Let it bubble for about a minute until the sauce is glossy and thickened.",
        "Add the pork back in and toss together to coat the pork with the sauce. Stir fry for a minute and plate.",
        "If used, cut up the beancurd sheets and blanch in hot water for a couple of minutes. Rinse and set aside.",
        "Drain the spring onions, and serve with the pork, stripped cucumber and duck pancakes or beancurd sheets."
